This paper deals with off-policy evaluation in reinforcement learning, which is a problem commonly studied in the machine learning community. The paper proposes a new method for bias reduction in infinite horizon off-policy evaluation, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of reinforcement learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves theoretical analysis and empirical experiments, which could place it in the categories of cs.ST (Statistics) and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
